  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nThere is an endless signing transaction process when trying to send two transactions in a batch. \nYou can check it in simpledapp.eth -> Transaction tab: the `Send two Txs in batch.` button.\n\nIt seems nothing to deal with failing transaction itself but bottom sheet, because once `Send transaction` bottom sheet is opened there is no way to close it (nothing happens when tapping `Cancel` button). Unlike to other bottom sheets in Dapp where all is OK.\n\nIt's all fine when sending single transaction or when sending two transactions one after another\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\nTwo Transactions sent fine from `simpledapp.eth` -> `Transactions` -> `Send two txs in batch`\n\n#### Actual behavior\n\nEndless spinner when trying to send two transaction in a batch from DApp\n\n<img width=\"290\" alt=\"Screenshot 2020-03-24 at 14 21 59\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/77425071-d873fe80-6dda-11ea-88f9-3d0c0b55f13a.png\">\n\n\n### Reproduction\n\n- Open Status and recover an account with funds\n- In Browser open `simpledapp.eth`\n- Open Transactions tab\n- Tap `Send two txs in batch, 0.00001 and 0.00002 ETH` button\n- Tap `Cancel` button (**Actual result**: nothing closed)\n- Sign transaction with valid password\n\n### Additional Information\n\n- Status version: develop nightly 23rd of March\n- Operating System: Android and iOS",
